      "y": 65216.74708664305,
      "width": 1232,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#fd7e14",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bbT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 199396599,
      "version": 194,
      "versionNonce": 105107255,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777046810450,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Instead of clustering items, you cluster users based on their browsing or order history. A user can\n  belong to multiple overlapping clusters based on different interests (e.g., one cluster for cheap electronics,\n  another for physics books)\n\n- Graph Databases (e.g., Neo4j): These are essential for collaborative filtering. User clusters and\n  order histories are loaded into the graph database to efficiently run specific queries, such as \n  identifying items that candidate users in your cluster have purchased, but you have not",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Instead of clustering items, you cluster users based on their browsing or order history. A user can\n  belong to multiple overlapping clusters based on different interests (e.g., one cluster for cheap electronics,\n  another for physics books)\n\n- Graph Databases (e.g., Neo4j): These are essential for collaborative filtering. User clusters and\n  order histories are loaded into the graph database to efficiently run specific queries, such as \n  identifying items that candidate users in your cluster have purchased, but you have not",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Mnt8Qa0yO3Cxkoistj8xX",
