    {
      "id": "bKO544wwaefs-tBLmjimj",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2321.1725833056503,
      "y": 66921.85634497524,
      "width": 1430,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#fd7e14",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bbV",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 294916631,
      "version": 450,
      "versionNonce": 580518839,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777046875689,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Once candidate items are found, the system predicts the rating the user would give to each item and sorts them in descending order\nto maximize the chances of the user liking the recommendation",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Once candidate items are found, the system predicts the rating the user would give to each item and sorts them in descending order\nto maximize the chances of the user liking the recommendation",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8LRuW-qjx9Lhwm4jAPgI1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2306.2967373655974,
      "y": 67024.08971718673,
      "width": 569.7998046875,
      "height": 35,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#fd7e14",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bbW",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 235890329,
      "version": 485,
      "versionNonce": 774796503,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777046875689,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "System Architecture and Data Pipeline",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "System Architecture and Data Pipeline",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "DKUHBMpMsj897LrNK2G_S",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2312.8804956304207,
      "y": 67104.13934064847,
      "width": 1551,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#fd7e14",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bbX",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 934812089,
      "version": 572,
      "versionNonce": 1817690615,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777046875689,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Ingestion: Distributed computing (like Spark jobs) reads data from product and order databases.It filters out low-quality items\n  (e.g., items with ratings lower than 3) to protect the user experience, and dumps the clean data into a central repository like S3.\n\n- Computation: Spark and ML pipelines run on the S3 data to train models and create the content/user clusters, storing the pre-computed\n  results back in S3 or pushing them to a Graph Database.\n\n- Serving: Because computing recommendations on the fly is expensive, a Recommendation Generator continuously processes data and stores \n  pre-computed recommendations for each user in a fast, key-value Recommendation DB.\n\n- Handling Exhaustion: When a user scrolls through all generated recommendations, the frontend triggers an event to the backend (via Kafka). \n  The recommendation generator acts asynchronously to quickly compute and add more items to the user's list.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Ingestion: Distributed computing (like Spark jobs) reads data from product and order databases.It filters out low-quality items\n  (e.g., items with ratings lower than 3) to protect the user experience, and dumps the clean data into a central repository like S3.\n\n- Computation: Spark and ML pipelines run on the S3 data to train models and create the content/user clusters, storing the pre-computed\n  results back in S3 or pushing them to a Graph Database.\n\n- Serving: Because computing recommendations on the fly is expensive, a Recommendation Generator continuously processes data and stores \n  pre-computed recommendations for each user in a fast, key-value Recommendation DB.\n\n- Handling Exhaustion: When a user scrolls through all generated recommendations, the frontend triggers an event to the backend (via Kafka). \n  The recommendation generator acts asynchronously to quickly compute and add more items to the user's list.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
